<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="facs">FACS</a> - A type offlow cytometry for sorting a mixture of <a href="#cell">cells</a> into two or more containers, one <a href="#cell">cell</a> at a time, based upon the <a href="#fluorescence">fluorescent</a> characteristics of each cell. Cells can be manipulated to express <a href="#fluorescence">fluorescent</a> properties in order to sort them by FACS.